John Sircombe","email":"3e9dc96b245271b56c5fb0a6f9aecf2122d7b8cb@arm.com"},"message":"Updates config=mkl_aarch64 build to oneDNN 2.4 and Compute Library 21.08

Updates oneDNN version used for `--config=mkl_aarch64` to 2.4
in line with x86 build.

Updates Compute Library (used as optimised oneDNN backend
on AArch64) to the latest release (21.08).

This enables support for SVE and BF16 kernels where
hardware supports.
This provides a performance uplift of between 1.4x and 3x
depending on the hardware support.

Removes some patches to oneDNN which are not required for
the 2.4 release.

NOTE: AArch64 build with --config=mkl_aarch64 requires GCC 10.

PiperOrigin-RevId: 403913180
Change-Id: Iae33d825a0d1f0bfc527d29f7670e48db141db3a","distinct":false,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/tensorflow/tensorflow/commits/5646333e1ece8170dff7b1980905e8f9c8383881"},{"sha":"82e5f70d8b19aef4b7185ec3bda1ca480623d8f6","author":{"name":"Frederik Gossen","email":"5bcb0c34b484f21048fb46d802116fb172e4e0a2@google.com"},"message":"[MLIR][KernelGen] Refactor MLIR-generated kernel registration to reduce bin size

Reduce template usage in MLIR-generated kernel registration to avoid the
generation of similar or even duplicate code. This change reduces the overall
binary size of OSS TF by 1.4 MB (uncompressed).

It also makes adding new JIT-compiled kernels much cheaper wrt. binary size as
kernel registration is one of the main costs here. The JIT-compiled `rint`
kernel for `f16`, e.g., now contributes only 2.66 kB (uncompressed) compared to
5.49 kB (uncompressed) previously.

[{"sha":"d4279bbe0abd54c32ab83886c875bea388b8955e","author":{"name":"Rahul Joshi","email":"15277936ae82919baaa227d3a37b5e73c80bf8d2@google.com"},"message":"Fix HLO->LMHLO conversion failure when constants are used in while loop condition.

- When lowering while, we call `GetOrCreateView` for the root of the condition, and then
  later import the entire condition computation in the whileOp condition region.
- For a constant condition, this means `GetOrCreateView` will populate the cache and
  later on when EmitConstant is called the second time during region import, it will fail
  since the cache is already populated.
- Address this by moving the HLO->MLIR cache for constants inside EmitConstant.
